inn1.comm: starts with a back of length ball outside off, left to the keeper
similar length just outside off, defended off the backfoot towards the off side
fuller this time, on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-on this time
length ball just outside off, Watson keeps bat and pad together as he defends solidly
back of a length and outside off, slashed off the backfoot towards backward point
length ball angling into the pads, a confident punch to mid-on, straight towards the fielder
length ball on the pads, tickled down to fine leg
back of a length ball just outside off, pushed towards cover
fullish ball on offstump, pushed towards mid-off, a sharp single is taken
that ball jumps up sharply, Watson was looking to defend from the crease, is struck on the wrists
short of length ball on the pads, a wonderfully timed clip off the pads send the ball racing to the square-leg boundary
fullish ball, punched towards mid-on

shout for lbw, turned down, pitching just outside off, and angling in, umpire thinks it's sliding down leg, and it hit the top of the flap of the back leg as well, Hawk-eye shows it's just hitting the top of leg, tough to give those
length delivery on the stumps, Haddin clips it towards mid off for a quick single
tried to flick a legstump delivery, doesn't get bat on a ball that should have been put away
another attempted flick, inside-edged onto the pads
eased towards mid-on for a single
lovely hit from Haddin, comes down the track and lofts the ball for a one-bounce four to long-on
dropped by Dowlin, simple chance to his left at second slip, Haddin looked to guide the ball towards third man, only gets it towards Dowlin, who really should have held on to that one
another drop, this was a much tougher chance though, Haddin absolutely lashed the ball back towards the bowler, who tries to catch the ball which is coming neck high at him but can't hang on
full ball just outside off, Haddin squeezes it into the ground and it reaches the keeper on the bouncer
shortish ball just outside off, Watson gets behind the line and defends off the back foot
half-volley on the pads, caressed wide of mid-on for a boundary, easy for Watson
even better from Watson, overpitched again, Watson takes a stride forward and slams the ball flat and straight for six
not a great over this for West Indies, the bowler oversteps as he sends down another full ball on the pads, driven towards mid-on
free-hit, a bouncer outside off, Watson hacks at it outside off, top-edge swirls over the head of cover point
length ball on middle and off, punched down the ground, mid-on moves across to his left to cut it off
back of a length and just outside off, played with an angled bat towards backward point
short of length outside off, defended solidly off the backfoot
short ball is pulled away by Watson, along the ground to deep square leg
overpitched on middle and leg, Haddin punches the ball towards mid-on, Pollard fields and throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end, Haddin had made his ground in time though
short and a bit of width, slapped past cover point by Watson
on the pads, short of length, defended towards the leg side
pulled by Watson, not along the ground this time, the fielder in the deep waqs interested for a while, but it lands short of him
wide down the leg side, just sprayed down Watson's pads
he like's that shot, just tees off down the ground with a big lofted shot off the front foot, intentionally hitting in the air and the ball goes miles up and beats long-on
better length, gets some cut, Watson nudges to the leg side
fuller ball, hit with hard hands across the line toward midwicket
shorter in length, Watson allows it come on and then rotates the strike with a gentle dab toward backward point, using the pace of the ball
turns this one off middle and leg to wide of backward square
slides down leg stumps, he swings and misses, the ball thudding off his pads to square leg
big heave to one on a length, dragging it to the leg side
again off the front foot, going at the ball hard, turning it toward mid-on

dropped at backward square leg, would have been a ripper! Watson flicks off his pads in the air, that ball was veering down and there for the hit, and Rampaul flings himself across to his left side but ends up parrying it away
short of a length, Haddin gets back and across and defends
gets back and defends again
shot! Fuller ball, angling in, and Haddin picks it up over mid-on
short ball, some turn, Watson goes back and punches to cover
slower in the air, dipping on the pads, clipped to midwicket
tosses up invitingly just outside off and down goes Haddin, kneeling before reaching out and slogging across the line, not a clean hit but it drops safely
flat and quick, goes back and cuts toward backward point
straighter one, slides on and just misses the bat as Watson is hurried into a late dab, just struck on the flap outside the line of impact, well bowled Miller
short and he rocks back to pull past midwicket for one
good ball to begin with, right up there on off and making Watson defend
shorter in length, no room on offer, and Watson goes back to block
good ball, on a length on off stump and Watson can only defend

well played, after three tidy balls Watson decides to take Sammy on, and does so to the half-volley with one of his preferred shots, the aerial drive over mid-on, hit through the line, and the ball sails over the man at long-on, superb shot
full on the pads and flicked out to the deep
nice drive to one floated up outside off, but he can't beat point
first ball of the over is defended solidly off the front foot
back of a length ball is punched down to long-on
fuller this time, tucked towards midwicket
shortish ball, just outside off, batsman makes room and slashes it towards backward point
sliding onto the pads, arm ball, turned towards short fine leg
on middle and leg, Watson stands tall and eases the ball towards mid-on
short of length ball just outside off, solidly defended
Watson misses out on that one, the fine leg is in the circle, the ball was on the pads, if Watson had got it past that fielder, it was four runs, but he glances it straight at him
shortish ball just outside off, carved towards backward point
driven down towards midwicket
a wristy whip towards deep square leg
Haddin glances it to backward square leg for a single
Haddin is down the ground, lofts the ball towards long-on, mistimed, reaches the fielder after a few bounces
a quicker delivery, driven to mid-on
floated up on the middle and leg, Watson blocks it
a wild throw form Sammy at cover, lobs it over the keeper after Watson pokes it towards him
this time Haddin charges out of the crease, gets to the pitch of the ball and clobbers it over long-on for six
what a way to bring up your half-century, Watson slams that one wide of long-on for a six
played down to short third man, straight at the fielder, so no run

well, that was a poor delivery to get out on, a full toss outside off, it was an attempted slower delivery, Watson looks to clear deep midwicket but his hoick can't clear the fielder there, a much-needed breakthrough for the Windes
full ball outside off, driven firmly back to the bowler
chops the ball towards backward point
back of a length and into the pads, tucked towards midwicket by Haddin
again on the pads, easily clipped towards square leg for another single
back of a length and just outside off, Haddin looks to guide the ball towards third man, doesn't beat the man in the ring
same length, just outside off, Haddin defends back towards the bowler
on middle stump, Haddin shuffles across and nudges the ball towards square leg
short of length and well outside off, Ponting gets forward and jabs the ball towards point
length ball just outside off, driven towards mid-off
length ball on middle, Ponting pushes it back towards the bowler's right
a touch shorter and outside off, slashed towards backward point, smart fielding there
easy single after punching the ball towards wide mid-on
almost a yorker, just outside off, Haddin blocks it towards the off side
short of a length and outside off, driven towards extra cover
well outside off, Ponting checks his shot to get the ball away towards backward point

bowled! not a replay Haddin will like to see again, the ball was miles outside off, Haddin was looking to mow it to the leg side, gets a bottom-edge that sends the ball onto the base of offstump, it's not been a great summer with the bat for Haddin
Clarke is greeted with a mis-directed bouncer, going down the leg side
length ball well outside off, Clarke watchfully lets it go
pushed off the backfoot towards cover point
back of a length ball on middle and off, defended towards mid-on
full and outside off, driven firmly to short cover
played with soft hands towards deep square leg, thinks of taking the second but decides against it
'Wait on' is the call after Clarke pushes the ball towards mid-on
this time the ball is driven to mid-on, Clarke charges out of the crease for a single but then heads back
Clarke leans across and flicks the ball from outside off past a diving mid-on, not enough on it to reach the boundary
chop a ball that is well outside off towards backward point

Ponting pulls a short ball, keeps it along the ground, a direct hit from the deep meant Australia could have taken an extra run, but the umpire Billy Bowden had already called for drinks, so they don't take it, Billy races towards the dressing-room as soon as the drinks van comes on
wide outside off, Ponting drives towards cover for a single
Clarke helps himself to an easy single after punching the ball to long-on
short ball just outside off, cut away towards point
waltzes down the track to a back of length ball, eases the ball to mid-on and zips through for a single
same length from Pollard, Ponting stands tall and punches past a diving short cover
length ball outside off, chopped towards backward point for a single to bring up the Australian 100
middle stump delivery, Clarke walks across and whips the ball to square leg
shortish ball just outside off, Ponting gets behind the line and defends back towards the bowler
short of length outside off, Ponting opens the face to steer the ball towards backward point
on middle and off, easy single by punching the ball towards long-on
Ponting gets the simple single this time, pushing the ball towards mid-off
'Wait on,' shouts Clarke after punching the ball towards cover off the front foot
on the pads, defended towards the leg side
again straying onto the pads, guided down to fine leg for a single
Pollard sends a slower ball, Ponting mistimes his shot, gets the ball away towards wide long-on though
this time Ponting shuffles across and helps the ball to short fine leg
Clarke punches the ball down the ground and helps himself to a single
short and a bit wide, Ponting slaps it towards sweeper cover
Ponting pulls the ball down to deep backward square leg
full and outside off, driven down towards mid-off for an easy single
Clarke continues to get the single by pushing the ball to long-on
shortish ball on off, Ponting punches off the backfoot towards cover
a bit of an edge as Clarke looks to carve the ball through off, trickles down to third man
defends a back of length ball outside off towards point
Clarke decides he's had enough of singles, charges down the track and hammers the ball over long-on for six
blocked towards mid-off this time by Clarke
pushed to mid-on off the front foot for a single
way outside the offstump, left alone by Clarke
pretty wide again, length ball, Clarke moves across and opens the face to steer the ball to third man
half-volley on the pads, thank-you says Ponting, easy put away to fine leg for four
sways back and chops the ball towards point
brushed off the thigh pad towards midwicket
waltzes down the track and pushes the ball to mid-on
turns the ball towards square leg, straight towards the fielder
length ball is driven to wide long-on for a single
short ball, turning towards legstump, Clarke stands tall and flicks the ball, but can't beat the man at square leg
driven towards sweeper cover for a single
on the pads, turned towards midwicket for a single
shortish ball just outside off, driven to short mid-off
driven to long-on this time for a single
clips a length ball on the pads towards midwicket
nudged to square leg this time, wide of the fielder, so they get a run
Clarke again dances down the pitch, clips the ball towards midwicket
makes room and chops a ball just outside off towards backward point
third single of the over, pushes towards cover this time
too close to the midwicket fielder to get a run
down the leg side, helped along to fine leg
more legstump offerings, dabbed to short fine leg again
Ponting goes big, came down the track and gave himself some room as well, clubbed it over long-off for six to bring up the 150
blocked back to the bowler this time
takes the easy single to long-on this time
this time it's Clarke who gives the man at long-on some fielding practice
carved towards sweeper cover
why don't they bring long-on in? again Clarke pushes the ball towards long-on and walks through for the single
gets back and cuts just wide of backward point for two
walks down and takes on the full, clipping past midwicket
slower ball down the pads, he sweeps fine and gets it well
walks out again, drives straight, Gayle falls as he intercepts
finer line and he nudges it out to square leg
lines up a big swipe to one tossed up, connects well out to Smith at deep square leg, who over-runs the ball
tossed up outside off, driven off the front foot to extra cover
fuller on the pads, he walks into the shot and clips it away
fuller ball, good use of the feet results in a drive to long-off
tossed up, no turn, walks across and on-drives
flatter and slower, he gets back and defends
takes it off the pads with a bunt but straight to midwicket
slowly floated outside leg and Ponting turns it away for one
shorter, just, but Clarke pounces and slaps it past point
goes back and hammers this one into the off side as well
tossed up on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
dances out and clips against the turn into the gap at square leg
another drop! Wider ball outside leg stump, Ponting gets down and sweeps very hard to square leg where Deonarine jumps up and goes for it above his head but spills it
tossed up, Ponting comes out and works it away
driven off the front foot down the ground for one more
goes back and punches the ball to extra cover and raises the bat
pushed across Clarke who reaches out and steers it off the face
better length and some drift too, Ponting drives off the front foot to cover
steps out on dancing feet and drives the ball down to long-off
again Clarke walks out and clips the ball on the full for a single
superb stroke for four! Ponting makes room to about the sixth or seventh stump and drives the flighted ball on the rise past extra cover
now he presses well forward and steers the ball to backward point, has a look up and sets off, Clarke responds but there's hesitation, then Hinds misses by some distance and they survive
comes forward and dabs the ball for one more
lovely shot, again he makes some room and this time lofts the ball over mid-off
tossed up on the pads and he drives away to midwicket
starts to press forward and then clips with the movement to square

tries the shot across the line again but this one is shorter and raps him on the flap as he steps across the sticks, cuing an enthusiastic and optimistic appeal, no chance that was out because of the shuffle and the height, so the result is a leg bye
comes forward and drives the ball down the ground
walks across again and works the ball past square leg
driven to cover, where the fielder deflects it away
ouch! Shorter in length, cuts back in sharply at a good height and smacks Clarke in the nether regions, pretty much flush, and down he goes to catch his breath

and he strikes first ball! Is he the one-day Graeme Swann? First ball of his spell, Pollard hits a length and as the ball angles across Ponting opens the face and runs it off the face to a tumbling Ramdin who holds on to a neat catch
full ball outside off, White walks into it and drives to cover
straighter ball, better length, and White keeps it out
tries a short ball but at  that pace it sits up like a tennis ball and White, getting inside the line, swats it past square leg for four
change of pace, fuller in length, pressed back with a full face
itching to come forward, White ends up adjusting to press it to point
presses forward, Rampaul bowls it shorter, Clarke drives to short cover where Gayle gets some bad bounce and gets struck above the wrist, wincing in pain
straighter ball, worked away to the leg side
good ball, short of a length and pressing White back, he then tries to dab it to the off for one but gets sent back as the fielder swoops in
shorter ball just outside off, allows it come on and then nudges it
walks back, Rampaul follows him, Clarke tucks it off the hips
good ball, on the stumps and rising, White presses it back
short outside off and he slaps it past square off the tiptoes to raise the 200 for Australia
leans into a full and wide ball and crashes it on the rise past cover
on a length and this time he drives on the rise down to long-off
short of a length, Clarke gets up and punches to mid-off
better length, White presses forward and has to defend
shorter ball, White gets up and slashes in the air wide of gully
gets up and turns the ball past midwicket, who gives chase
nice and straight on a length and its driven back to Rampaul

well there's an easy dismissal, but it looked tense for a few seconds! Rampaul digs it in, Clarke gets up to ride the bounce and turn the ball past midwicket but gets a leading edge that balloons up toward mid-on, Hinds runs in from the other side but its Deonarine from short midwicket who calls for it and takes it as he tumbles over with Hinds staring
gets up and edges a short ball into the gap behind point
short of a length on the hips, turned away to open his account
pressed onto the back foot, he gets up and pushes to midwicket
pitches it up and Voges presses off the front foot
short ball, cut off the back foot toward cover-point
slower ball on the legs, on-driven to the fielder
comes forward and goes hard at the ball, ends up checking the shot
stabs at one clipping in and turns it to the leg side
shorter in length and he goes back before turning it to midwicket
back of a length and this is defended back to Smith
shorter in length, White steers it away wide of backward point
loud shout as a faster one aiming at leg stump just raps the pad as Voges attempts the nudge, he's late on the stroke but that ball was just doing too much
presses forward and nudges the ball back down the track for one
back of a length, gets back and pushes the ball to Smith
much fuller and this time he drives a nice-looking shot between extra cover and mid-off
too straight so White works it away toward square leg
gets across and works this one to deep square leg
short of a length on middle and off, White presses forward and adjusts to defend, it goes on the bounce to Sammy's right and he sticks out a hand
loose drive outside off to a fuller one that pitches and deviates
on the walk, White drives on the rise to extra cover
shorter ball, Voges gets his back leg across and punches to cover
punched on the rise to the off side
straighter ball, short of a length, pushed back to the bowler
gets some room and slashes a good shot behind point
full and wide, so he reaches out and drives between cover and point
full down leg stump, tries the flick and gets rapped on the boot
overpitched on the stumps, White makes room and drives to long-off
driven off the front foot down the ground
shorter length, straightens after pitching, Voges gets up to work it away but the extra bounce draws a leg bye off the pads wide of Ramdin
comes forward and pushes to the off side
gets over the short ball and pulls in front of square for a couple
gets another shortish ball and nudges it up past square leg
fuller ball on middle and leg and White on-drives a single
short ball to begin with, forces him up on the hop, defending to leg
another short ball, this time White goes back and slashes uppishly and backward point does the fielding, fumbling after stopping to allow the single
third short ball, this time down the stumps, and Voges gets across to pull to fine leg
short of a length, Voges gets up and cracks it toward point
fourth short ball in a row, down the leg side, White is late on the pull and the ball kisses his gloves through to Ramdin who moves across to his left and holds on
now he pitches one up and Hopes drives confidently to cover
flicks off the pads but cannot beat short fine leg
on the stumps and he clips nicely just wide of midwicket
better length but still he drives down to long-off for one
wider ball, smacked to Gayle in the covers
full toss which is turned wide of square leg, there's a fumble out there
goes for a yorker and doesn't quite manage it, Voges plays to mid-on
gets up and muscles a short-arm jab wide of mid-on
first four of the Powerplay, as Hopes makes room and bangs the short ball over point
short down the stumps, brushes his pads and trickles fine
much fuller and flicked out to deep square leg for one
nice and full and straight and Hopes whiplashes it to long-on
short ball gets him rising and slicing to backward point for a quick single
full and driven down the track to Smith
uses his feet and clips this one away past square leg
low full toss, bunted in the air safe of midwicket
full and straight and driven toward extra cover
shorter in length, he fends it away in front of square leg
in the blockhole and he works it to midwicket and sets off
clears his front leg and slogs back in the air fiercely, Rampaul sticks out a hand but cannot stop it, Hinds is sluggish in the deep and he gets four
nice shot! Rampaul digs it short, Hopes hooks and beats square leg
now the attempted yorker-length ball outside off, but same result, as Hopes squeezes it past gully and gets four more

and dropped! Oh what a terrible day of fielding for West Indies! Rampaul should have had Hopes, who moves aside and drives on the air down the ground but Hinds, running in from long-on, makes a meal of a straightforward catch, in and out of his lap, shocking piece of work down there
now he goes to the on side and drills this ball past extra cover
serves up a full toss, Hopes walks out and drives it over Rampaul and down to long-off who does the fielding
short ball down the stumps, he backs away and slogs over midwicket out to the deep where Nash, the sub, doesn't pick it up and reacts late
uses his feet and pushes it away for one more
makes room but cannot connect well on the near yorker, yet steals one
good placement from Voges, who hops up and cuts the short ball in the air smack between cover and point
follows up with a full and straight ball, Voges clears his toes and drives down the ground
now he tries the lap shot and pulls it over pretty well, just reaching across and taking if from just about off stump and placing it past short fine leg
short of a length to Voges who steers it down to third man
full and wide, he backs away and throws the bat at ball and misses
nearly a yorker but too full, chipped in the air over mid-on out to that man Hinds who doesn't pick it and the ball goes over his palms
this time a chip shot, using his wrists, over mid-on as he reaches to outside off
good ol' fashioned slog, just heaving across the line over midwicket
bad ball, very wide down the pads, Hopes shuffles but can't connect
yorker outside off, he steers it down to Sammy at third man for one
tossed up outside off, slightly short, Hopes gets back and cuts behind point, the sweeper cannot cut it off and there's an excellent half-century
hah, easy pickings! Makes room, dances out, and drills it over extra cover
low full toss but Hopes doesn't put it way, instead driving to long-off
floated down the stumps, Voges sweeps and gets it tangled up off his arm, then into the pads
awesome chip shot from Voges, skipping out to the ball and then lofting high and handsome for a straight six
speared in, Voges makes room and drives and gets an inside edge past leg stump

inn2.comm: starts with a length ball on middle., Gayle moves across awkwardly and works it to square leg

Bollinger strikes second ball, pitching on back of a length on legstump, hitting just above the knee roll with the batsman on the crease, massive appeal, umpire has little doubt, Hawk-Eye suggests the ball would have just gone over the bails
length ball outside off, edged away through backward point
a touch fuller this time, on middle and leg, Gayle stays back and works the ball towards backward point
lost his radar there, swinging way down the leg side, Haddin dives across to collect, good work that
length ball on middle and off, Deonarine playing off the backfoot, jumps and defends towards the bowler
same length, a bit of width on offer, batsman swings at it, gets an edge past backward point
starts with a fullish ball just outside off, blocked towards cover
back of a length, on off, defended off the backfoot towards point
similar length, on middle and off, tucked off his thigh pad towards square leg
length ball outside off, left alone by the batsman
on middle and leg this time, blocked off the backfoot towards the leg side
full and just outside off, driven firmly to mid-off, and that's a maiden
shortish ball, Gayle goes for the pull, it's the top-edge, crowd gets excited thinking there's a catch at fine leg but the ball sails over the rope
and another top-edge six, not as short as the previous one, again goes for the pull, another top-edge, soaring over slips and the third man boundary

Gayle remains Bollinger's bunny, what an over this has been, Gayle opens  the face, gets a bit of an outside edge towards short cover, Clarke latches on to an overhead catch there, Bollinger has two, that's the fourth time he has dismissed Gayle
solidly defended, getting on the front foot, and blocks
again Pollard gets behind the line and defends back down the pitch
back of a length, on middle stump, Pollard taps the ball towards midwicket
length ball outside off, pushed towards sweeper cover for a quick two
back of a length on middle and leg, defended awkwardly off the back foot
same length but outside off, blocked towards point
full and pitching on off, more defence from Deonarine
Windies lose another, Deonarine slashes at a length ball outside off, gets a bottom-edge which flies back onto off stump, Australia's unbeaten summer is set to continue
big appeal for lbw, turned down by the umpire
fullish ball outside off, defended by Pollard towards the bowler
back of a length on legstump, brushed off the thigh pad towards backward square leg
angling across the batsman, who drops his wrists and sways out of the line to let the ball go
angling across the batsman, who lets it go again
back of a length on the leg stump, clipped to fine leg for a single
full and just outside off, punched crisply to mid-off
pace and bounce, sits up wide off and wide called
too straight, tucked to Smith at backward square leg
pitches on a length outside off, some shape, left alone
good length on off stump and he's forced to defend
shorter in length and still Pollard is made to defend
just a bit full and he presents a full face of the bat, pushing the ball past mid-off, really a good stroke from Pollard
hops across and twirls the bat of ball's way as it passes
pitches on a good area and gets Hinds pushing to the off side
smashes this one, a wee bit fuller, on the up and evades a leaping mid-off, that was hit without much footwork but Hinds made sure he went hard and fast, Voges does the fielding in the deep
good length ball angles across and he leaves it be
and again he works the ball across Pollard who leaves it be
fuller in length and Pollard plays it straight to mid-off
bit wider and there to be hit, Pollard drives but can't beat mid-off
drives off the front foot, nice and straight, back down the track
angles wider this time and Hinds watches it through to Haddin
now he wafts at the identical delivery outside off and gets beaten
lovely channel being worked here, on a length outside off, not full, not short, and it keeps Hinds in two minds and this time he decides to leave well enough be
straightens the line to off stump and Hinds punches to cover
back to that teasing spot about a foot or so outside off and Hinds leaves
starts off down leg stump with a short ball which Pollard lets pass
fuller outside off and straightening, Pollard starts to leave but the ball clips the other half of the angled bat and runs to third man
overpitched and driven firmly toward mid-off where Bollinger falls to his right and saves three runs, big man that and he hits the ground with a thud, well stopped
short of a length and defended to the off side
full and straight and well flicked off the pads in front of square
thrashes that one on the rise, looking to go downtown, but misses
short of a length and Pollard gets nice and tall to defend
on a length and he pushes a straight drive to mid-off
short of a length on the stumps, worked to square leg
out comes the big heave now, not timed too well but he goes up over midwicket, drops safely in the deep

there's a catch to the rookie! Short ball comes onto Hinds quicker than he probably anticipates and he's all at sea trying to pull and Smith runs across from square leg, calling for it, and takes it in front of midwicket
full on middle and leg and clipped past square leg to the sweeper
ah, driven on the rise off the front foot, but not with a big stride forward, and Pollard pops the ball tantalisingly over the covers
short of a length outside off to Simmons who tries to play, then leave, but as the bat twirls it clips the ball and rolls to backward point
brings him onto the front foot this time and he defends
gets back nicely and forces this ball to backward point where Ponting allows the ball through his legs
short of a length, wee bit of cut, steered to Ponting who does well now
goes back and bunts the shorter ball past square leg
fuller in length, driven to Smith on the circle at midwicket
comes forward and pushes the ball back to the bowler
straighter ball off a shorter length, he tries the nudge but gets hit on the flap
too fine and it sneaks past leg stump to Haddin
good length delivery, Pollard pushes it to Hopes' left side
well that took off! Pitches on a length and zips up off the deck, surprising Pollard who presses forward and then does well to drop the hand and rear away
legcutter to end the over, defended toward point
short of a length to Simmons who gets tall and defends to point
comes forward and then defends to backward point
straighter ball, good length though, and he defends it back
very watchful stuff this, Simmons defending off the front foot
hops back to a shorter ball and steers it straight to point again
excellent over from McKay, ending with one short of a length to get Simmons hopping back in line and defending to cover
offcutter, short of a length, Pollard stands tall to drive and gets an inside edge onto his thigh
walks out, Hopes digs it in short, draws the top edge on the pull, Haddin runs back a long ways but that is six
back of a length, some shape, this time he defends
fuller and now he clips it off the stumps to deep midwicket
nicely played, Pollard gets across the sticks and taps the ball to square
drives a fuller ball to backward point's left side
lovely shot there, just pirouetting on the short ball and getting maximum over midwicket
right up there on off stump and he turns it to the leg side
back of a length, pushed off the back foot to Smith at midwicket, who runs around and flings himself to his left to save a single
goes back and pushes the ball to the leg side again
shorter ball, Pollard starts walking across and then rides the bounce and angles the ball to place it wide of Smith for a single
goes back to tap the ball off the pads to square leg
goes back and punches an offcutter to the covers
tries something different, walking forward and across the sticks, then flicking straight to Smith at midwicket who releases and hits the bat
pitches on a length, Simmons drives on the up to cover
again he uses his crease in an attempt to manipulate the bowler, works it to square leg and Smith runs after the ball and slides to stop
ah, now a loose chip shot as Pollard loses a hand off the bat, just takes it from outside off and manages to beat mid-on and midwicket
nice steer off the front foot but straight to backward point
takes on the short ball with a controlled pull through midwicket
goes deep in his crease and uses the wrists to turn the ball to midwicket
now he gets some groove going, moving back and across and pummeling the ball over mid-on for four
now he punches an on-drive to mid-on and puts pressure on Bollinger
cuts back in off a fuller length and Pollard works it past midwicket
short ball, Pollard swivels and bunts past square leg
lovely shot there, just pirouetting on the short ball and getting a beefy six over midwicket

nice catch there Smith! Hopes tries the short ball again, Pollard obliges with a much squarer pull shot, not as controlled at the previous one, and a running Smith takes it at deep backward square leg
hops across and shoulders arms to one outside off
goes back and keeps this one out too
short of a length, Simmons hops in line and defends
slashes a leaden-footed shot outside off and gets beaten
tosses it up and lands it nicely, Smith drives it back.
fuller ball, Smith clips it to midwicket
gives it some air, gets some dip, Smith heaves and beats mid-on, Bollinger dives, the ball wins the race
wrong 'un, middle and leg, stabbed at in defence
driven off the front foot, Smith runs across, mid-off runs in
fuller and flatter with some drift into leg stump, Simmons loses balance as he jams the ball to the off side
reaches out and drills the length ball down to mid-off
pitches on a length and he keeps bat and pad together while blocking
hits a shorter length and jumps up to beat the bat
fuller and he pushes tentatively at it, turning past midwicket
gets inside the line of this short one, hopping across the sticks, and runs it down to backward square leg
presses forward and dabs the ball to mid-on for a quick single
tossed up on middle and leg and Smith prods it back
big shot this time, Smith clearing the front foot and swinging the ball over long-on for half a dozen
flatter ball, Smith goes back to dab it fine but is beaten for bounce
goes back in the crease and pushes the wrong'un to midwicket
floats it up just outside off and Smith drives off the front foot to point
goes back and cuts the shorter ball to Hopes at short third man
gets up to the short ball and works the wrists, lapping the ball past midwicket
back he goes, punching this ball to point
well played, sees room outside off and brings the bat down firmly to back-cut past point, leaving third man with plenty of work but he has no chance
gets outside the line and pushes the ball to cover for a single
pitches back of a length, Smith walks across and turns it to leg
fuller ball, on-driven straight to White at midwicket
too short and Simmons cuts past short third man for four more
tossed up down the pads, worked off the front foot to square
nicely floated up on a length, getting Simmons driving to long-off
slower through the air and that results in some dip, but Smith hits across the line to midwicket
slides down the pads and he gets a touch on it
lines up a flat-batted swipe that beats Bollinger at cow corner
slapped! Simmons greets Bollinger by backing away and charging and slamming the ball down past mid-off, straight as a whistle and fiercely struck
well played again, rising to the short ball and angling the bat to work it past midwicket

short of a length on off stump, Simmons goes back and across and pushes to cover, takes a step forward, then hesitates, at the other end Smith sets off but gets shooed back and that does him in as Clarke nails a direct hit, superbly fielded there in the covers and West Indies lose their sixth
gets back and works the short ball past midwicket, Smith chases and releases
nice and straight and Simmons presents a full face of the bat
on a length, no room on offer, tapped straight to point
low full toss first ball, which Ramdin bunts to wide of midwicket
goes back and plays his preferred cut shot to backward point
flat ball, no turn, he goes back and punches it
fuller and slower, pitches on leg and he plays it to midwicket
drifts in, too short though and that is punched of the off side
better line, drifts in and he plays it with a stride forward

smacked but straight to Clarke at cover! Bollinger drags it short as Simmons goes to the leg side, looking to smack it down the ground, and the result is a flat-batted slap into the vice-captain's lap, that was hit hard and should leave a sting, but well held
welcomes him with a bouncer, Sammy flinches and takes his eyes off it
gets across gingerly and defends the ball to midwicket
angles across and now Sammy shoulders arms
fuller ball, squirted off the front foot past Ponting at backward point
full on the stumps, clipped with the movement to midwicket
better shot, gets to the pitch and drives handsomely to extra cover
super shot, just gets the high elbow in play and launches a length ball over mid-off
flatter ball, he comes forward and defends
slides in, this time he works it to the leg side
shuffles and glances the ball around the corner

plumb and Smith has his first ODI wicket! Tossed up, pitches in line with the sticks and straightens a touch, the sidespin does the trick as Ramdin plays for turn and is hit in front and the Australians rush to congratulate a red-faced Smith
goes back and puts the short ball into the covers for two
full outside off, beats the bat
on the stumps, no room at all, and he has to defend
and again, right up there, some cut, and that's defended back
shorter in length, Sammy is surprised and stabs at it and the ball runs off his gloves to the leg side
pushed across and he shoulders arms
and again he gets forward and shoulders arms
swats this one across the line and beats midwicket and mid-on
slower ball, more flight, fuller and wider too, it pitches and turns and takes the edge past slip
wrong' un on middle and leg and he defends it back
comes forward and drives the fuller ball to mid-off
too short and Sammy punches off the back foot to cover
another appeal as the wrong' un strikes the front pad, but there were two sounds and that puts the doubt in the umpire's mind, which replays show was the right move
back of a length outside off and no shot offered
just a bit shorter and he defends to the off side
gets up on the toes to again push the ball in front of cover
good shot, a flowing straight drive to one pitched, bang past mid-on
goes back to that shorter length and Sammy goes back to defending
gets up and slices the shorter and wider ball past backward point
tossed up, no turn, driven off the front foot into the cover for one
flatter and straighter and Sammy pushes off the back foot to point
pitches on a length and that's driven over mid-off to long-off
flatter ball drifts in and he works an inside edge off the pads
tossed up, comes forward and drives to the off side
floated up on middle and off and he slashes it past cover
gets back and works the ball off the stumps to midwicket
on the stumps and he defends to the off side
straighter ball, Miller pushes it back, Harris sticks out his right hand and misfields
down the pads, turned to midwicket
goes for a big smash this time and mistimes it to long-off
good short one gets some lift and surprises the batsman
tossed up on middle and leg and Sammy drives it back to Smith
another firm drive, high elbow and all, but straight to cover
good shot, gooood shot! Sammy goes downtown and latches on well, grabbing the tossed up ball and lofting high and high over long-on for six
flatter, expectantly, and he plays it back past Smith
goes back and nudges the ball off the pads
edged wide of Clarke at slip, neither forward nor back, feeling for it
presses forward to a length ball and runs it wide of point
shorter in length and he runs it to point too
reaches out to cut but cannot beat cover or point
gets nice and tall and pushes the ball to point
nicely driven on the rise over extra cover, freeing the arms, good shot
shorter ball and pulls uneasily down to long leg with an edge
flighted on the stumps, Sammy takes it off the front pad for one
short and flat, Miller chops it into the covers for one more
again too short and Sammy punches it to extra cover
another flowing shot from Sammy against Smith, skipping out and hitting straight through the line, dumping that over cow corner for the biggest six of the day
dropped in the deep! Sammy pulls a half-tracker over midwicket, out to where David Hussey runs across a long way and dives but cannot hold on
gets back and pushes the ball away

end of a frustrating stand as Miller is forced up by a short ball and slaps it to Clarke at cover, he stands there for a while thinking the ball was too high, but no reaction from the umpires and West Indies lose their ninth
gets back and pushes at the ball, point runs in
gets over it and pushes it away again
hits a length and moves away, Rampaul is squared up and edges to point, Ponting collects and hits the stumps and Rampaul gets an overthrow
hits a good length, Sammy pushes at it uneasily outside off
too short so Sammy deposits that over mid-on's head for four
no turn, pretty short, and Rampaul goes back to block
fuller and wider and now he slashes over the covers, but Sammy sends him back after they run two
out comes the slog sweep which gets him a single
comes out but cannot connect on the loopy delivery, wasn't to the pitch and ends up pushing it down the ground for a single

stumped and it's all over! Rampaul thows his bat at the one that drifts away, dragging his back leg marginally forward, Haddin collects and breaks the sticks, yelling out a relieved "THANK YOU" as he does so, and replays show Rampaul's foot was on the line so that is the end of that
